An easy way of finding a vector linearly independent to 
                        \Vect{x}
                      is to find a nonzero vector which is perpendicular to 
                        \Vect{x}
                     .

Look for a nonzero vector which is perpendicular to 
                        \Vect{x}
                     .

A nonzero vector perpendicular to 
                           \Vect{x}
                         is 
                           \Vect{y}:= (2,0,-1)
                        . This implies that 
                           \Vect{x}
                         and 
                           \Vect{y}
                         are linearly independent.
